        <section class="question-long-text" data-uuid="a3b85a2c315a40aaa5a12708c0cc1e97">
            <object type="text/html" data="../../assets/widgets/long_text_question/index.html" class="widget" data-uuid="946c9348511a4950be2a339f8e03ca22">
                <param name="configFile" value="../../widget_data/config/946c9348511a4950be2a339f8e03ca22.json" />
            </object>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="82f6449e0c964f06a303f70fb9352b56">About 180,000 African Americans served with the Union army. They initially received $10 a month, while white soldiers got $13. In June 1864 Congress passed a bill granting African American soldiers equal pay.</p>
        <section class="image-carousel" data-uuid="1737cdb929ec4c7a9fb006a8202b2a37">
            <object type="text/html" data="../../assets/widgets/image_carousel/index.html" data-uuid="5e5e395e45ec4d9eb61cbc4c60e9e556">
                <param name="configFile" value="../../widget_data/config/5e5e395e45ec4d9eb61cbc4c60e9e556.json" />
                <param name="credit" value="[null,null]" />
            </object>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="971f73ae6a8445fcad83177b03790646"> African Americans faced special horrors on the battlefield. Confederates often killed their black captives or sold them into slavery. In the 1864 election, Lincoln suggested rewarding African American soldiers by giving them the right to vote.<br />
        </p>
